HEADWORD: Cœnesthesis
<hw>C⟦oe⟧n`es*the"sis</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>koino`s</grk> common + <?/ sensation.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Common sensation or general sensibility, as
distinguished from the special sensations which are located in, or
ascribed to, separate organs, as the eye and ear. It is supposed to
depend on the ganglionic system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

